attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, for GNU/Linux 2.6.32, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a malicious downloader. It establishes a connection to a hardcoded C2 server at 49.232.102.63 on port 8081. It then downloads a next-stage payload, decrypts it using a single-byte XOR with key 0x99, and executes it directly from memory using memfd_create and fexecve (a fileless execution technique). To evade detection, it uses '/tmp/log_de.log' as a mutex to ensure only one instance runs and masquerades its process name as '[kworker/0:2]'.
